commentTextItems.html: there it is! India win by four wickets! good length delivery on the pads and that's clipped over the fielder at midwicket

commentPostTextItems.html: India reach the target with one over to spare and they now lead the seven match series 2-0.

It was a modest total but the England bowlers bowled beautifully and made a match out of it, Sehwag and Gambhir gave India a good solid start putting on 61 runs for the first wicket but India soon slipped to 92 for 5 in the span of just 11 overs and it looked like the England bowlers would have the final say...

but Raina and Dhoni had other plans, they added 118 runs for the 6th wicket and that put India back on top, they curbed their natural instinct and played the ball on the merit and in the end it turned out to be a match-winning partnership, Raina went on to make 81* runs for which he gets the Man of the Match award.
